hello ! Verdatim here.
So you want to add more stuff for scripted mags huh?
Well heres how it works for CURRENT set up 13/6/26 (DD/MM/YYYY)

First lets go to the hardest case, if you just want to add an existing mag model to a gun (i.e. a magazine section that already has a model attached to it in "scripted_magazines.script"'s "mag_models" table)
then the steps are as follows
	1. Open the model using ogf editor and find the name of its mag bone
	2. Create a DLTX file (or use the one included) and add the section of your gun.
	3. Create the fields as follows under the gun section
		s_magazine_hide_bones = [YOUR MAG BONE NAME(s)]
		s_magazine_positions_[MAG BONE NAME] = x,y,z
		s_magazine_rotations_[MAG BONE NAME] = x,y,z
		s_magazine_scale_[MAG BONE NAME] = float
		s_magazine_parent_bone_[MAG BONE NAME] = [MAG_BONE_NAME]
		(btw the parent bone name does not have to be the mag bone name itself, if for some reason you want to attach it somewhere else)
	
	4. Open up the game
	5. The gun should have the mag model attached properly, but the reloads wont swap the magazines just yet
	6. Find the hand animation and its corresponding omf that your gun uses
	7. In that omf, add an "lmg_reload" motion mark and time it to where you want the mag models to swap
And thats it! it should be working once you relaunch the game

ADDING NEW MAGAZINE MODELs:
preferably, you should try to align the mag models and their bones so they all line up
Then add the sections and models associated to the "scripted_magazines.script"'s "mag_models" table
